        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('National Semiconductor'); ?>
        <p><strong>National Semiconductor</strong> was an American semiconductor manufacturer which specialised in analog devices and subsystems, formerly headquartered in Santa Clara, California, United States. The company produced power management integrated circuits, display drivers, audio and operational amplifiers, communication interface products and data conversion solutions. National's key markets included wireless handsets, displays and a variety of broad electronics markets, including medical, automotive, industrial and test and measurement applications.</p>
        <p></p>On 23 September 2011, the company formally became part of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Texas Instruments', 'C'); ?> as the "<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Silicon Valley', 'IT'); ?>" division.</p>
